  25.  def registerTask(taskId: TaskId, location: TaskLocation): RegisterTaskStatus

    When a task is booted, it need to call registerTask to register itself.

    When a task is booted, it need to call registerTask to register itself. If this task is valid, then accept it, otherwise reject it.

    taskId

    Task that register itself to TaskRegistry.

    location

    The host and port where this task is running on. NOTE: The host and port is NOT the same host and port of Akka remoting. Instead, it is host and port of custom netty layer, see io.gearpump.transport.netty.Context.
